      <h1 class='title'>Drugs Budget</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 cc277-8WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_277ws' title='Col. 277WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c277WS' name='column_277ws' href='#column_277ws' rel='bookmark'>277WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06419'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_360'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-chris-grayling' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_360' title='Link to this speech by Mr Chris Grayling' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-chris-grayling" title="Mr Chris Grayling">Chris Grayling</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06419">To ask the Secretary of State for Health what information he has assessed on spending levels on drugs in acute hospitals in<span class="italic">(a)</span> the last year for which figures are available and <span class="italic">(b)</span> each of the past three years. [88740]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-06420'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_361'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-john-hutton' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030108_CWS2_361' title='Link to this speech by Mr John Hutton' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-john-hutton" title="Mr John Hutton">Mr. Hutton</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-06420">The information requested is shown in the table.</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_278ws' title='Col. 278WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 January 2003 vol 397 c278WS' name='column_278ws' href='#column_278ws' rel='bookmark'>278WS</a><p id="S6CV0397P0-06421"><table>
          <tr>
          <td><span class="italic">Total expenditure on drugs for NHS trusts in England</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td></td>
          <td>&#x00A3;</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td><span class="italic">Total expenditure on drugs for NHS trusts in England</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td></td>
          <td>&#x00A3;</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td>1998&#x2013;99</td>
          <td>1,208,098,376</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td>1999&#x2013;2000</td>
          <td>1,360,825,466</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td>2000&#x2013;01</td>
          <td>1,515,722,071</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td>2001&#x2013;02</td>
          <td>1,683,684,266</td>
          </tr>
          </table></p><p id="S6CV0397P0-06422"><span class="italic">Source:</span></p><p id="S6CV0397P0-06423">NHS Trust Financial Returns 1998&#x2013;99 to 2001&#x2013;02.</p><p id="S6CV0397P0-06424">The data include total expenditure on drugs, gases and blood products (but not fresh blood from blood centres) for national health service trusts in England. Drugs expenditure alone cannot be identified.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
